commText: So the words ‘KL Rahul’, ‘strike rate’ and ‘intent’ will be discussed across sporting circles once again. But can’t take anything away from the way SRH obliterated this chase. We doubt many could achieve the strike rates that Abhishek Sharma and Travis Head are recording even while playing book cricket or hand cricket. Never before have so many runs ever been scored in the first 10 overs of an IPL game. Never before has anyone at Cricbuzz been able to switch off their laptops before 11pm during an IPL game. Grateful for that early finish, this is Saurabh Shankar signing off on behalf of Pradeep, Kumar, Akshay and Siva.

Travis Head | Player of the Match: Lot of fun today. Nice to get this done in 10 overs. Abhi and I have had a few partnerships like this. Just concentrate on getting in good positions, watch the ball hard and try to maximise the powerplay. (On his spin hitting) It is something I have been working on, it will be a big part in the Caribbean as well. It is important to go 360 in the modern game. (On fearless cricket) The last 12 months, that's how they wanted me to play in the Aussie team, and that's what I've been told to do here as well. Nothing much that I have to change. (On Abhishek Sharma) I know how hard he works and how deep he thinks, his spin play is second to none. We compliment each other very well. Nice to see him back amongst the runs after missing out the last couple of game. (On NRR) We didn't think about it till the Timeout, but after that the boys came out and told us to score quickly. The crowd was exceptional tonight, that's what we needed after losing the last two. I haven't got many things over him, so that's good to know that I have more runs than David Warner did in his first SRH season. We start again whenever we come out here for the next game.

Pat Cummins: (On did he change the pitch) Maybe Travis and Abhishek did. We just let them go, they are two guys who are very positive and I'm a bowler, it is tough for me to give them any inputs. (On Travis Head) He's been like this for 2 years, he hits the tough areas, hits the middle a lot, might not be super conventional. (On Abhishek Sharma) Just an incredible player of spin and pace. With just 2 fielders out, it is really difficult for the bowlers against them. (On where the game is headed) I think the scores have gone up, and when the wickets are good, it is tough to come up with answers against batters when they get going. The boys have had a fantastic season, but to win this with less than 10 overs played is unreal.

So this result means that Mumbai Indians have been eliminated from the playoffs race. This is also the first win for SRH over Lucknow.

Abhishek Sharma: I would never think of coming to such a tournament and playing at such a strike rate, but thanks to the team management. The message was clear from them and I backed myself. All the credit goes to him (Head). The way he starts against all bowlers.. he goes after them from the start and takes the pressure off. The bowlers told us (during the innings break) that it was getting better, but myself and Travis thought it was not doing much. I think the hard work I put in before the tournament is showing now, thanks to Yuvi Paaji, Brian (Lara) as well and my father, who is my first coach.

KL Rahul: Am lost for words. We have watched that kind of batting on tv. But this is unreal batting. Everything seemed to find the middle of the bat. Kudos to their skills. They have worked hard on their six hitting skills. They didn't give us a chance to know what the pitch played in the second innings. Was hard to stop them as they teed off from ball one. Once you are on the losing side, there are questions marks on the decisions taken. We were 40-50 runs short. When we lost wickets in the powerplay, we couldn't get any momentum. Ayush and Nicky batted well to get us to 166. But even if we would have got 240, they could have chased it as well.

22:16 Local Time, 16:46 GMT, 22:16 IST: Between both innings today, it feels like we got a classic microcosm of how the T20 game has evolved in the last few years. Gone are the days when you can play out powerplay with conservative strike rates, with the hopes of maximizing output in the death overs. The modern T20 cricketer believes in carnage, believes in clearing that front leg and whacking it to all parts of the ground. It is no longer about winning games, it is about obliterating oppositions with net run rates facing fatal consequences. Travis Head and Abhishek Sharma made batting look easier than EA Cricket on amateur mode, as they devoured into the LSG bowlers, inflicting a brutal loss to the visitors. The first over went for just 8 runs, and that was the only joy LSG got the whole innings. Abhishek Sharma dispatched Thakur for four consecutive boundaries, and then Travis Head latched onto Gowtham, plundering 22 runs off it. The Aussie batter scored a 16-ball fifty, as SRH finished the powerplay with 107 runs. Abhishek Sharma wasn't too far behind, as he got a 19-ball fifty. The hitting never stopped even after the fifties, as both batters went hell for leather to help SRH chase down the target in less than 10 overs. Stick around for the presentations...

Yash Thakur to Abhishek Sharma, SIX, all over!! A back of length delivery angling outside off. Abhishek Sharma waits for it and slaps it over wide extra cover for a maximum. This game has finished before the second time-out. What a thumping performance from SRH. Once again a Pat Cummins team peaking at the right time?
Yash Thakur to Head, 1 run, pushes it very wide outside off on a length. Head goes chasing and gets it off the bottom towards extra cover. Rushes through for a single
Yash Thakur to Head, 2 runs, length ball angling outside off, slapped down the ground for a couple of runs
Yash Thakur to Abhishek Sharma, 1 run, wide yorker, Abhishek Sharma slices it towards sweeper cover
Yash Thakur [2.0-0-37-0] is back into the attack
Naveen-ul-Haq to Abhishek Sharma, 1 run, length ball at the stumps, pushed towards mid-on for a single
Naveen-ul-Haq to Abhishek Sharma, no run, cutter that angles across outside off, goes under the bat. I0$
Naveen-ul-Haq to Abhishek Sharma, FOUR, pace off and down leg almost, Sharma tickles it away towards the fine leg boundary. Sprinkles some finesse onto all this brute force..
Naveen-ul-Haq to Head, 1 run, hard length ball on off, slapped don to long-on

Naveen-ul-Haq to Head, SIX, call the cops, I'd like to report a murder! The murder of LSG's net run rate. Nothing too wrong with this ball, it was almost a yorker. Slightly undercooked and Head manages to get under it and scoop it into the stands beyond long-on
Naveen-ul-Haq to Head, 2 runs, pace off length ball, Head makes some room and slaps it down the ground. Stopped by long-on, couple of runs taken
Naveen-ul-Haq [1.0-0-23-0] is back into the attack

Ravi Bishnoi to Abhishek Sharma, SIX, I0$ Abhishek Sharma dances to the pitch of this one and casually chips it over wide long-on for a maximum. These two southpaws are genuinely making it look easier than a video game on easy mode!!
Ravi Bishnoi to Abhishek Sharma, no run, dropped!! Fired full on middle, Sharma drills it powerfully back at Bishnoi who gets a hand to it by jumping to his right. Very tough chance, goes begging..
Ravi Bishnoi to Head, 1 run, fired onto off stump, driven down to long-off

Ravi Bishnoi to Head, SIX, into the second tier!! Travis Head clears his front leg and slogs it deep beyond mid-wicket for a maximum. The World Cup is in USA, perhaps Travis Head can try his hand at baseball too, the way he is going. Cricket seems too easy for him!!
Ravi Bishnoi to Head, no run, pushed quicker and spinning away, beats Head as he tried to cut

Ravi Bishnoi to Head, FOUR, is this a real IPL match or is this EA Cricket 07? Ravi Bishnoi's googlies have been difficult for most to hit, but Travis Head stays back and slices his cut square of the wicket for a nonchalant boundary
Ravi Bishnoi [1.0-0-17-0] is back into the attack
Ayush Badoni to Abhishek Sharma, FOUR, goes inside out now!! Dances to the pitch, makes room and curves his drive to the left of sweeper cover for a boundary
Ayush Badoni to Head, 1 run, fired in onto the legs, pushed down to long-on
Ayush Badoni to Abhishek Sharma, 1 run, dances down a bit and pushes it down to long-off
Ayush Badoni to Abhishek Sharma, SIX, gentle length ball onto middle stump. Abhishek Sharma rocks back and smokes it over long-on. Into the second tier it goes. That's a 19-ball 50 for the southpaw
Ayush Badoni to Head, 1 run, sliding onto leg from a length, pushed down to long-on
Ayush Badoni to Head, SIX, powerplay or not, Travis Head isn't changing his approach!! Rocks back to this short ball and pulls it over deep mid-wicket for a maximum
Ayush Badoni, right-arm off break, comes into the attack
Time-out. Who wanted the time-out? I guess we needed it more. 59 needed off 84 balls.

Yash Thakur to Abhishek Sharma, SIX, fuller one, outside off, Abhishek Sharma gets under it and lofts it over wide long-off. He climbed into that delivery and put it away with elan. 107 off 6 overs have been robbed. This game is gone. LSG's worst nightmares have come true. They have 150 seconds to recall the onslaught...
Yash Thakur to Abhishek Sharma, no run, slower one, outside off, Abhishek Sharma looks to heave it away and misses. That landed on a bounce to the keeper

Yash Thakur to Abhishek Sharma, FOUR, 100 up off 34 balls. Slower one, outside off, Abhishek Sharma slams the drive and hits it hard past the bowler for a four. Hit hard and into the fence. SRH had an eye on the NRR. And other team have their eyeballs on this pair...

Yash Thakur to Abhishek Sharma, SIX, short ball, angled in, at the body, Abhishek Sharma pivots on the back foot and slams it over fine leg. Huge hit and six more. They have 97 on the board. The rate needed is less than 5 per over now
Yash Thakur to Abhishek Sharma, no run, I rubbed my eyes! DOT BALL. Slower one, outside off, Abhishek Sharma left it alone as that was close to the tramline

Yash Thakur to Abhishek Sharma, FOUR, Sharma doesn't want the limelight to be solely on Head. Abhishek Sharma backs away and creams the square drive past point for a four. Poor effort from the fielder. That should have been stopped
Yash Thakur [1.0-0-17-0] is back into the attack

Highlights (Overs 1-5) - Gowtham opens the bowling - Abhishek smashes Yash for 4 fours - Head v Gowtham - 6, 0, 4, 6, 6, 0 - SRH openers bring up the 50 in 3.1 overs - Yash drops Abhishek on 24, Bishnoi the unlucky bowler - Even Bishnoi is taken for 17 runs - Head smashes a 16-ball fifty - Head v Naveen - 4, 4, 6, 4, 4

Naveen-ul-Haq to Head, FOUR, guess what happened? Yeah, you are right. Four again. Slower, outside off, Head backs away and slaps it past cover for a four. That was hit hard and into the gap. 87 from 5 overs. Just give them the game. Where's the towel?
Naveen-ul-Haq to Head, FOUR, yawn...yawn...four more. Backs away, slaps it over cover and four more. That was a slower delivery, Head got the room and powered it over cover

Naveen-ul-Haq to Head, SIX, fifty off 16 balls. All HEADS MUST BOW TO THIS HEAD! That was a length delivery, outside off, Head backed away and slammed it wide of long-on. He is on song. That song is noise to LSG fans for sure. I just want to know which flight does Head needs to catch?

Naveen-ul-Haq to Head, FOUR, now only 93 needed. Four more. Back of a length delivery, slower, Head got on top of the bounce and slapped it wid eof the man at mid-off. He managed to infuse enough power into the shot
Naveen-ul-Haq to Head, FOUR, spills it wide outside off and Head slaps it over cover. That was muscled by Head as he got the room outside off
Naveen-ul-Haq to Abhishek Sharma, 1 run, stabs it down with soft hands and steals a single. Abhishek Sharma wants the best seat in the house to watch Headplay
Naveen-ul-Haq, right-arm fast medium, comes into the attack

Ravi Bishnoi to Head, SIX, this is insane! This is unreal. Was a flatter googly, outside off, Head got back and slapped it over long-off. Awesome power and superb balance at the crease to put it away. Head has made heads turn at this IPL and he continues to do so
Ravi Bishnoi to Head, no run, goes back to a googly and slaps it to the man at point. Was hit well by Head
Ravi Bishnoi to Head, no run, flatter one, Head slaps it back to the bowler who stops it to his right with a dive. That was hit well by Head
Ravi Bishnoi to Head, FOUR, goes back and slaps it past cover. Was a googly and he climbed on to it. Good shot again

Ravi Bishnoi to Abhishek Sharma, 1 run, and dropped! The move almost paid off. That was a delivery which spun away, Abhishek Sharma looked to slog it and got it off the edge. Thakur leapt up to his right but got a hand to it only. Good attempt but failed to grab it

Ravi Bishnoi to Abhishek Sharma, SIX, this is massive. This is six more. This is pandemonium at Hyderabad. It rained earlier. Now it is raining sixes. Was on a length, angled across, Abhishek Sharma stayed his crease and kept his balance to launch it over long-on. Fifty up off 19 balls
Ravi Bishnoi, right-arm leg break, comes into the attack
Gowtham to Head, no run, backs away, Gowtham follows him and Head stabs it down into the deck. Head affords a smile. Gowtham is elated that the over is over now. They have raced to 47 now...

Gowtham to Head, SIX, on the knees, out of the park. Yawn. So used to this chaos when this duo is out there. Was a tossed up delivery, Head kept his head still and launched it down the ground to send it over the ropes

Gowtham to Head, SIX, straight down the ground for a sixer again. Stayed back, used the depth of the crease to slam it off the back foot and over the bowler's head for a sixer. SRH as I mentioned earlier want an early finish
Gowtham to Head, FOUR, he is too good off his hips! Went back and lofted it over short fine for a four. He is unstoppable
Gowtham to Head, no run, goes back and punches it hard to find the man at cover
Gowtham to Head, SIX, straight down the ground for a sixer. Chipped down, got to the pitch of the ball and lofted it over long-off. Superb hit. He didn't try to hit it hard

Yash Thakur to Abhishek Sharma, FOUR, that's a massive over! SRH fans are used to this. Was a delivery on to the pads, Abhishek Sharma looked to heave it away and managed just about enough bat on it to get it past the dive of the keeper

Yash Thakur to Abhishek Sharma, FOUR, backs away and plays it in a deft manner to play it between short third and point. Got inside the line of the delivery and managed to control the shot to get it into the gap
Yash Thakur to Abhishek Sharma, wide, slips it down leg and has been wided. Abhishek Sharma wanted to heave it away

Yash Thakur to Abhishek Sharma, FOUR, length delivery, at 137.3 kph, Abhishek Sharma hops away and creates room to thread the ball through the off-side. Five inside the circle and he found the gap past cover point
Yash Thakur to Abhishek Sharma, FOUR, little dragged down delivery from Yash Thakur and Abhishek Sharma climbs on top of it and pulls it down to deep mid for a four. Picked the bones out of that
Yash Thakur to Abhishek Sharma, no run, devoid of room, on a length, at the sticks, stabbed back to the bowler
Yash Thakur to Abhishek Sharma, no run, angles in, Abhishek Sharma tucks the ball down to mid-wicket
Yash Thakur, right-arm medium, comes into the attack
Gowtham to Head, FOUR, angled in, quicker one, on the pads, Head goes back and pulls it wide of short fine for a four
Gowtham to Abhishek Sharma, 1 run, flatter one, outside off, slapped wide of long-off for a single
Gowtham to Abhishek Sharma, wide, slips it wide and down leg and has been wided
Gowtham to Head, leg byes, 1 run, slower one, on the pads, nudged down to short fine and they sneak in a single. There was a direct hit at the bowler's ended but he made it easily
Gowtham to Head, no run, nudges the ball down to find the man at mid-wicket
Gowtham to Abhishek Sharma, 1 run, flatter one, Abhishek Sharma slaps it over the bowler's head. Mistimed and only a single
Gowtham to Abhishek Sharma, no run, stabs it down into the off-side
Abhishek Sharma and Head are at the crease. Abhishek Sharma is on strike. Gowtham will open the attack
